\section{Background}
Compositionality refers to the principle that the meaning of an expression is determined by its parts and their syntactic combination. In neural network terms, this requires that internal representations capture the shared attributes of components when they appear in different contexts. Prior work has often relied on modifications to network architectures or training routines to induce compositional behavior. In our work, we take a different tack by directly adding a regularization term that measures the discrepancy between hidden representations of related inputs.

